## v1.1.0 (2026-05-26)

**Changed by:** 5-PR parallel swarm false-positive fix wave (PRs #1937, #1959, #1960, #1965, #1978)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- Added Step 7 "False-positive escape catalog" covering 4 new rules:
  - MD033/no-inline-html on `<placeholder>` in prose → backtick-wrap recipe
  - MD018/no-missing-space-atx on line-start `#NNN` → reflow or `\#NNN` recipe
  - MD059/descriptive-link-text on `[link]`/`[here]`/`[click]` → use subject as link text
  - MD056 on non-GHA pipes (CLI syntax, regex alternation) → same `\|` escape as GHA
- Extended When to Use with 4 new trigger conditions
- Extended Step 1 failure-type triage table with 4 new rows
- Added 5 new Failed Attempts rows documenting tried-and-failed approaches
- Added 5 new Verified On entries for the swarm PRs
- Added frontmatter `verification: verified-ci`
- Added tags: MD033, MD018, MD059, false-positives

### Why

v1.0.0 covered the structural failures (MD056 inside GHA expressions, MD060, mkdocs
out-of-tree links, CLAUDE.md trim, shared-link drift). It did NOT cover the broader
class of false-positives where markdownlint misinterprets ordinary prose as syntax
violations. The 5-PR swarm produced a tested catalog of escape recipes for the four
most common false-positive patterns. Adding them here keeps the catalog comprehensive
rather than splitting into a sibling skill.

